  <h1>iPad Mini Review</h1>
  <div class="content"><p>I&rsquo;ve had the iPad mini for maybe a week now. Before I even went out to buy it, I&rsquo;ve had experience with the regular sized iPads, but I always felt that they were way too big to carry around without looking like you&rsquo;re slightly crazy. I wanted to buy it so I could put all my books for college on it instead of carrying books around. Carrying books around is just not fun in my opinion, and I&rsquo;m not sure why I never did this in college before now.</p>

<p>So far I&rsquo;ve enjoyed the iPad. I haven&rsquo;t had many problems with it as of right now either. The only thing that would be nice is if it could connect to a 4G network without having to pay for that. That being said, I should mention that I only got the wifi iPad becuase I did not want to pay for a plan for an iPad. That&rsquo;d just be silly unless I was in places where I needed it.</p>
</div>
  <time>This post was published by Luke Evers on 2013-09-03 at 18:31</time>
